If you're planning to get into Data Analytics, Data Science, AI, ML, or Data Engineering, learn:

1⃣Statistics & Mathematics – Especially probability, linear algebra, calculus, and inferential stats

2⃣MS Excel, SQL, & Power BI – For data manipulation, reporting, and dashboarding

3⃣Python – With libraries like Pandas, NumPy, Matplotlib, Scikit-learn, etc.

4⃣Databases – Relational (e.g., MySQL, PostgreSQL) and NoSQL (e.g., MongoDB)

5⃣Data Cleaning & Wrangling – Using Python (Pandas) or SQL

6⃣Data Visualization – Tools like Power BI, Tableau, or Python (Seaborn, Plotly)

7⃣Machine Learning – Supervised, unsupervised, model evaluation, using Scikit-learn or TensorFlow

8⃣Big Data Tools – Spark, Hadoop, or Databricks (especially for data engineering)

9⃣Cloud Platforms – AWS, Azure, or GCP (focus on data-related services like S3, BigQuery, Redshift, etc.)

🔟Version Control – Git & GitHub for collaboration and tracking

1⃣1⃣APIs & Web Scraping – Using Python (Requests, BeautifulSoup, Selenium)

1⃣2⃣Projects & Portfolio – Build real-world projects and showcase them on GitHub and LinkedIn

1⃣3⃣Soft Skills – Problem-solving, communication, storytelling with data

1⃣4⃣Domain Knowledge – Understand the industry you're targeting (finance, healthcare, retail, etc.)

1⃣5⃣Job Readiness – Resume building, mock interviews, case studies, and Kaggle competitions.

If you're planning to get into Data Analytics, Data Science, AI, ML, or Data Engineering, learn:

1⃣Statistics & Mathematics – Especially probability, linear algebra, calculus, and inferential stats

2⃣MS Excel, SQL, & Power BI – For data manipulation, reporting, and dashboarding

3⃣Python – With libraries like Pandas, NumPy, Matplotlib, Scikit-learn, etc.

4⃣Databases – Relational (e.g., MySQL, PostgreSQL) and NoSQL (e.g., MongoDB)

5⃣Data Cleaning & Wrangling – Using Python (Pandas) or SQL

6⃣Data Visualization – Tools like Power BI, Tableau, or Python (Seaborn, Plotly)

7⃣Machine Learning – Supervised, unsupervised, model evaluation, using Scikit-learn or TensorFlow

8⃣Big Data Tools – Spark, Hadoop, or Databricks (especially for data engineering)

9⃣Cloud Platforms – AWS, Azure, or GCP (focus on data-related services like S3, BigQuery, Redshift, etc.)

🔟Version Control – Git & GitHub for collaboration and tracking

1⃣1⃣APIs & Web Scraping – Using Python (Requests, BeautifulSoup, Selenium)

1⃣2⃣Projects & Portfolio – Build real-world projects and showcase them on GitHub and LinkedIn

1⃣3⃣Soft Skills – Problem-solving, communication, storytelling with data

1⃣4⃣Domain Knowledge – Understand the industry you're targeting (finance, healthcare, retail, etc.)

1⃣5⃣Job Readiness – Resume building, mock interviews, case studies, and Kaggle competitions.

If you're planning to get into Data Analytics, Data Science, AI, ML, or Data Engineering, learn:

1⃣Statistics & Mathematics – Especially probability, linear algebra, calculus, and inferential stats

2⃣MS Excel, SQL, & Power BI – For data manipulation, reporting, and dashboarding

3⃣Python – With libraries like Pandas, NumPy, Matplotlib, Scikit-learn, etc.

4⃣Databases – Relational (e.g., MySQL, PostgreSQL) and NoSQL (e.g., MongoDB)

5⃣Data Cleaning & Wrangling – Using Python (Pandas) or SQL

6⃣Data Visualization – Tools like Power BI, Tableau, or Python (Seaborn, Plotly)

7⃣Machine Learning – Supervised, unsupervised, model evaluation, using Scikit-learn or TensorFlow

8⃣Big Data Tools – Spark, Hadoop, or Databricks (especially for data engineering)

9⃣Cloud Platforms – AWS, Azure, or GCP (focus on data-related services like S3, BigQuery, Redshift, etc.)

🔟Version Control – Git & GitHub for collaboration and tracking

1⃣1⃣APIs & Web Scraping – Using Python (Requests, BeautifulSoup, Selenium)

1⃣2⃣Projects & Portfolio – Build real-world projects and showcase them on GitHub and LinkedIn

1⃣3⃣Soft Skills – Problem-solving, communication, storytelling with data

1⃣4⃣Domain Knowledge – Understand the industry you're targeting (finance, healthcare, retail, etc.)

1⃣5⃣Job Readiness – Resume building, mock interviews, case studies, and Kaggle competitions.
